### Describe the bug
Type `IAllowAnonymous` was moved as breaking change and the [announcement](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/aspnetcore#authorization-iallowanonymous-removed-from-authorizationfiltercontextfilters) recommends to use:

```csharp
var endpoint = context.HttpContext.GetEndpoint();
if (endpoint?.Metadata?.GetMetadata<IAllowAnonymous>() != null)
{
}
```

But `<IAllowAnonymous>` value always defaults to `null or undefined` and is not present in `Metadata?`

### To Reproduce

Use the above code snippet in method for `HandleAuthenticateAsync()` in `AuthenticationHandler<T>` when creating custom authentication handler:

```csharp
public class CustomAuthenticationHandler : AuthenticationHandler<AuthenticationSchemeOptions>
{
   public const string Scheme = "Custom";

    public CustomAuthenticationHandler(
            IOptionsMonitor<AuthenticationSchemeOptions> options,
            ILoggerFactory logger,
            UrlEncoder encoder,
            ISystemClock clock)
            : base(options, logger, encoder, clock)
        {
        }

     protected override async Task<AuthenticateResult> HandleAuthenticateAsync()
     {
            var endpoint = this.Context.GetEndpoint();
 
            // Check for [AllowAnonymous] present on method
            // this is always null and not present in Metadata?
            if (endpoint?.Metadata?.GetMetadata<IAllowAnonymous>() != null)
            {
                return await AuthenticateResult.NoResult();
            }

            return await AuthenticateResult.Fail();
     }
}
```

2. Use `[AllowAnonymous]` attribute on controller method:
```csharp
public class HomeController : Controller
{
    [AllowAnonymous]   // doesn't show up in Metadata.GetMetadata<IAllowAnonymous>();
    public string Foo => "Bar";
}
```

3. Mention in Startup
```csharp
public void ConfigureServices(IServiceCollection services)
{
     services.AddTransient<IHttpContextAccessor, HttpContextAccessor>();
     
     // Authentication
     services.AddAuthentication(auth => {
          auth.AddScheme<CustomAuthenticationHandler>(CustomAuthenticationHandler.Scheme, "Custom");
     });
}

// Configure method snippet
app.UseAuthentication();
app.UseAuthorization();
```

### Exceptions (if any)

Value `endpoint?.Metadata?.GetMetadata<IAllowAnonymous>()` is not present on `Endpoint.Metadata` even with `[AllowAnonymous]` present.

